      title: "How Much Is Kitchen Fitting Labour Per Day?",
      metaDescription: "Kitchen fitting labour in Coventry and Warwickshire costs approximately £300–£400 per day. Find out what a day's labour involves and how to estimate your total.",
      answer: "Kitchen fitting labour in Coventry and Warwickshire typically costs around £300–£400 per day. Install My Kitchen charges approximately £350 per day, with most kitchens taking between 3 and 10 days depending on size and complexity.",
      takeaways: ["Daily labour rate in Coventry/Warwickshire: approximately £300–£400/day", "Install My Kitchen charges approximately £350 per day", "Small kitchens: 3–4 days; medium: 4–6 days; large: 6–10 days", "Labour is the main variable in total installation cost"],
      body: `<h2>Kitchen Fitter Labour Rates in Coventry and Warwickshire</h2><p>Kitchen fitting is a skilled trade and labour rates reflect this. In the Coventry and Warwickshire area, you should expect to pay approximately £300–£400 per day for a qualified, experienced kitchen fitter. Rates below £250 per day should be approached with caution — at this price point, either the fitter is rushing the job, lacks experience, or the rate does not include everything needed for a complete installation.</p><h2>What Does a Day's Labour Include?</h2><p>Our day rate covers all aspects of kitchen installation including cabinet assembly and levelling, wall fixing, worktop cutting and fitting, door and drawer fitting and adjustment, handle fitting, plinths, cornices and finishing trims, appliance fitting, and snagging. It does not include plumbing, electrical or gas work, which are carried out by qualified tradespeople.</p><h2>How to Estimate Your Total Labour Cost</h2><p>Multiply the number of installation days by the daily rate to get your base labour cost. For a medium kitchen (13–20 units) at 5 days × £350/day, the labour cost is approximately £1,750. Add worktop fitting (typically £200–£600 depending on material and complexity) and appliance installation (typically included in the day rate) to arrive at a total installation cost.</p><p>This estimate does not account for particularly complex layouts, island installations, or premium German kitchens which require more time. The pre-installation survey provides a fixed quote that removes this uncertainty entirely.</p>`,
      faqs: [
        { q: "Do kitchen fitters charge VAT?", a: "Whether VAT is charged depends on whether the fitter is VAT registered. Install My Kitchen will confirm VAT status when providing your quote following survey." },
        { q: "Is it cheaper to hire a sole trader or a company?", a: "Sole traders may charge slightly less than companies with overheads. The key is experience and quality of work rather than business structure. Always ask to see examples of previous installations." },
        { q: "Can I reduce costs by preparing the room myself?", a: "Stripping out your existing kitchen yourself can save one day of labour. Ensure all waste is cleared and surfaces are protected before the fitter arrives. Discuss this with your fitter before doing any strip-out." },
        { q: "What should I expect to pay in total for kitchen installation?", a: "Total installation costs typically range from £1,800 for a small kitchen to £7,500 for a large, complex kitchen. This includes all labour, worktops and finishing. Book a survey for an accurate fixed quote." },
