      body: `<h2>Kitchen Installation Costs in Coventry</h2><p>Coventry homeowners typically pay £1,800–£7,500 for kitchen installation, depending on the size of their kitchen and the complexity of the project. These figures are consistent with the national average for the West Midlands region and reflect the labour rates and market conditions in the local area.</p><h2>Cost by Kitchen Size</h2><p>The most reliable way to estimate installation cost is by kitchen size:</p><ul><li><strong>Small kitchen (8–12 units):</strong> 3–4 days, £1,800–£2,800. Common in Coventry's terraced properties and 1960s semis.</li><li><strong>Medium kitchen (13–20 units):</strong> 4–6 days, £2,800–£4,200. Typical of larger semis and detached properties across Earlsdon, Allesley, Stivichall and Kenilworth.</li><li><strong>Large kitchen (21+ units):</strong> 6–10 days, £4,200–£7,500. Found in larger detached homes, open-plan extensions, and properties in Leamington Spa, Warwick and Solihull.</li></ul><h2>Local Factors Affecting Cost</h2><p>Coventry's housing stock is varied, from Victorian terraced properties in Earlsdon and Chapelfields with typically smaller kitchens and potentially uneven walls and floors, to post-war semis across the suburbs with more straightforward room conditions, to newer executive detached properties with open-plan kitchen-diner layouts that tend to be larger installations.</p><h2>Getting an Accurate Quote</h2><p>The figures above are ranges — the only way to get an accurate price for your specific Coventry home and kitchen is through a pre-installation survey. Our survey costs £195, credited back on booking, and provides a fixed installation quote.</p>`,
